description: Catch us with Mexican style coffee brewed with fresh cinnamon sticks and breakfast burritos in Downtown Oakland. Enjoy warm tacos and tortas after work during Uptown happy hour. Our three-wheel bike can even makes house calls, as long as  it’s local. We will roll up to your backyard, private party or fiesta in the park. Founder, Alfonso Dominguez, co-owns La Calle Asadero and Tamarindo Antojeria restaurants with his mother, Gloria Dominguez. Both restaurant locations are in Downtown Oakland and offer traditional regional Mexican cuisine.  La Calle Asadero is the true inspiration for El TacoBike, as the more casual eatery, which focuses on traditional Mexican street food like tacos, tortas, gorditas and fresh aguas frescas—all offered on the mobile menu.
name: El Taco Bike
